# Color & Theme Usage

- **Use global theme variables**: Always use colors defined in `global.css`, Tailwind config, or shadcn theme tokens (e.g. `bg-primary`, `text-muted-foreground`, `border-border`) instead of hard-coded hex, rgb, or hsl values.
- **Avoid static color literals in UI code**:
  - In React/Next.js components, do **not** use inline styles with raw colors (e.g. `style={{ color: "#ff0000" }}` or `style={{ backgroundColor: "red" }}`).
  - In CSS, SCSS, or other style files, avoid raw `#hex`, `rgb(...)`, or named colors; prefer CSS variables from the theme (e.g. `var(--primary)`, `var(--muted-foreground)`).
- **Follow shadcn theme tokens**: When using shadcn UI components, prefer the documented semantic classes (`bg-background`, `text-foreground`, `bg-secondary`, etc.) and extend via theme tokens rather than introducing new arbitrary colors.
- **Centralize new colors**: If a new color is needed, add it once to the global theme (e.g. in `global.css` or Tailwind config) and reference it by variable or token, rather than inlining it where it is used.

## Examples

```tsx
// ❌ BAD - hard-coded color in component
<div style={{ backgroundColor: "#ff0000" }}>Alert</div>

// ✅ GOOD - use theme class
<div className="bg-destructive text-destructive-foreground">Alert</div>
```

```css
/* ❌ BAD - hard-coded hex */
.custom-badge {
  background-color: #0ea5e9;
}

/* ✅ GOOD - use theme variable */
.custom-badge {
  background-color: var(--primary);
}
```

